                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra name of the protagonist of Text II,
                           name of the donors and his family members; elements of the punctuation
                           signs, of the text dividers and of the quire marks; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals.
 Several groups of lines on the incipit pages of Texts I-1
                           and II, alternating with black lines; initial two lines of each section
                           of Text I, II, V, VI, and of each miracle of Texts III and IV; the words
                           salām “salutation” and sǝbḥat “glory” in Text VI; first word of each
                           stanza in Text VI.</seg>
